<br>
I died in Scarlet Desert.  After I died I spent about 15 minutes checking to see if there were any clerics about who could help me, then I camped.<br>
<br>
I logged in the next day and dragged my corpse closer to the zone line to Twilight.  This took me about 25 minutes tops.<br>
<br>
Then I signed in about four more times, each time for under 2 minutes, checking for clerics.<br>
<br>
The last time I signed off, I checked the rezz timer on my corpse and it had 58 minutes left.  I /camped and exited completely out of EQ as fast as I could, spending no time on the server select screen, other servers, or the log in screen.  Then when I logged back in, I conned my corpse and had 50 minutes left.  So basically, about 7 minutes ticked down even after I had camped and closed EQ.<br>
<br>
I don't know what the deal is.  I had been offline way more than 3 hours before getting resurrected, but I wasn't online for more than a hour and a half, yet apparently the game ticked down about 2 hours and 10 minutes.<br>
<br>
I do know that the rezz timer ticks down even if you are logged in, like on the server select screen, playing on another server, or in chat.  So that might be what got you.  Still doesn't completely explain my experience, but oh well.<br>
<br>
Of course, we all know better to expect consistency from Verant.  If their patch message says a /note window is added and old /note command functionality is preserved, don't be surprised when there is no new /note window and the /note command is broken.  If their patch message says a new line of Shadow Knight spells has gone live and is selling the Echo Caverns, don't be surprised when there's not a single vendor in the entire game selling new spells. <p><B><FONT FACE="Comic Sans MS">--Tukka</FONT></B><BR>
